<p>Quality Prosecco displays a pale straw to light golden color, with premium examples showing brilliant clarity and persistent, fine bubbles that rise in elegant streams. The <strong>perlage</strong> (bubble formation) reveals crucial quality indicators—finer, more persistent bubbles suggest superior production methods and fresher wine. Younger Proseccos maintain that crystalline straw hue, while aged examples may develop deeper golden tones, though most are designed for immediate consumption.</p>

